  \begin{remark} \label{remark:1t}
      For general objective functions with Lipschitz continuous gradients, the optimal convergence rate is $\mathcal{O}(1/t^2)$ by using Nesterov fast gradient methods, see~\cite[chapter~2]{Book_Nesterov_2004}.
